(1837: t. 1970) in the leaves being pendulous, linear, semiterete with upper surface concave and v-shaped, fleshy, not planar in transverse section; sepals ciliate with hairs more than 
<quantity id="4CCF9B328078FFBB1DC2E0B6C129F83A" box="[1215,1289,2024,2045]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF48665F807BFFB819F5E1F1C60AF92E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5153695" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5153695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5153695/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28" startId="2.[136,229,1711,1733]" targetBox="[144,1445,219,1636]" targetPageId="2">
